# Exclude everything by default, then re-include only what the image needs.
*

# Re-include the build inputs the Dockerfile copies (Node server + static site).
!server/
!server/**
!site/
!site/**

# Never ship installed deps into the build context — the image runs `npm ci`.
node_modules/
**/node_modules/

# Belt-and-suspenders: explicitly drop internal/business docs and VCS/CI cruft.
# (These are already excluded by the `*` rule above, but listed for clarity so
# they can never accidentally land in the build context or image.)
CLAUDE.md
dugri_plan.html
resources/
.git/
.github/
.netlify/
*.md
.DS_Store
**/.DS_Store

# The API also spawns the Python generator (previews + order PDFs), so the image
# needs the generator code AND the theme assets it reads at runtime. Re-include
# them AFTER the blanket excludes above so these rules win.
#
# Generator code, recipes, themes.json and the shared word-font pool.
!generator/
!generator/**
**/__pycache__/

# Each theme's clean/ background SVGs + fonts/ are all that the render path reads.
# Re-include the whole templates tree, then drop the heavy filled/ reference
# exports (Canva calibration renders, not used at runtime) to keep the image lean.
!resources/
!resources/canva/
!resources/canva/templates/
!resources/canva/templates/**
resources/canva/templates/*/filled
resources/canva/templates/*/filled/**
